      • testNreadRandomAcessFile

        public void testNreadRandomAcessFile(java.lang.String path,
                            int positions,
                            int level)
        This method tries to open a existent file determined by path and read it randomly starting in "position" and put text inside a string variable. The read stops when end of file is reached or limited by level. This method is a call to native c/c++ function.
        Parameters:
        path - Determines the path to the file that will be randomly read.
        positions - Determines the position where will be started the read.
        level - Determines the size of string variable that will receive the read text.

      • testNwriteRandomAcessFile

        public void testNwriteRandomAcessFile(java.lang.String path,
                             int positions,
                             java.lang.String stretch)
        This method tries to open a existent file determined by path and writes the "stretch" in position determined by "positions" parameters. This method is a call to native c/c++ function.
        Parameters:
        path - Determines the path to the file that will be randomly read.
        positions - Indicates the position where the stretch will be written.
        stretch - Is the part of text that will be written in the file.
